PETSc's per-package `requires32bitintblas` defaults to 1, which makes
configure reject any external SuiteSparse when paired with 64-bit BLAS
indices.  Julia's stdlib SuiteSparse_jll is built against libblastrampoline
and works correctly with 64-bit (`_64_`) BLAS symbols at runtime, so the
check is too strict for our setup.  Override it to 0 in SuiteSparse.py.

This applies cleanly to PETSc 3.24.x.

diff --git a/config/BuildSystem/config/packages/SuiteSparse.py b/config/BuildSystem/config/packages/SuiteSparse.py
index 1234567..89abcde 100644
--- a/config/BuildSystem/config/packages/SuiteSparse.py
+++ b/config/BuildSystem/config/packages/SuiteSparse.py
@@ -5,6 +5,7 @@ import config.package
 class Configure(config.package.CMakePackage):
   def __init__(self, framework):
     config.package.CMakePackage.__init__(self, framework)
+    self.requires32bitintblas = 0
     self.minversion        = '5.6.0'
     self.version           = '7.11.0'
     self.versioninclude    = 'SuiteSparse_config.h'
